Offers of equipment and personnel for San Francisco Bay earthquake survivor searches   came from Los Angeles, Los Alamos, Israel, and France.
LA shipped doctors, police, and  fire investigators.
British engineers came to assess structural damage.
Charleston sent   drinking water, symbolic of support following Hugo.
The Salvation Army dispatched 12  mobile canteens.
The Red Cross, strained by Hurricane Hugo, opened 25 shelters.
Its   LA, San Diego and Portland offices sent blood.
Osaka, Japan promised $10,000.
Anheuser-Busch sent canned water.
The Coast Guard sent boats and helicopters.
The IRS  waived late-filing penalties.
President Bush planned to visit and promised $273 million  victim aid.
San Francisco estimated $2 billion damage. 
